## 2026-03-28 - Search doesn't highlight matched substrings
- Rewrote `highlightMatch()` to accept an array of terms and highlight all occurrences using a single regex (longest-first to avoid partial overlaps).
- Added `searchHighlight` memo in `TokenList.tsx` that parses the raw search query via `parseStructuredQuery` and extracts `nameTerms` (free text + `name:` + `path:` qualifiers) and `valueTerms` (free text + `value:` qualifiers).
- Changed `TokenTreeNodeProps.searchQuery` to `searchHighlight: { nameTerms: string[]; valueTerms: string[] }` — group names, token names, and value displays all highlight matched substrings.

